00:00:06,850 --> 00:00:09,250
MY NAME
IS MELINDA GORDON.

2
00:00:10,450 --> 00:00:12,850
I'M MARRIED,
I LIVE IN A SMALL TOWN,

3
00:00:14,050 --> 00:00:15,350
AND I OWN AN ANTIQUE SHOP.

4
00:00:15,850 --> 00:00:17,150
I MIGHT BE JUST LIKE YOU.

5
00:00:18,050 --> 00:00:19,750
EXCEPT THAT FROM THE TIME
I WAS A LITTLE GIRL,

6
00:00:19,750 --> 00:00:21,250
I KNEW THAT I COULD
TALK TO THE DEAD.

7
00:00:22,350 --> 00:00:23,650
Grandmother:
IT'S ALL RIGHT, HONEY.

8
00:00:23,650 --> 00:00:25,450
EARTHBOUND SPIRITS,
MY GRANDMOTHER CALLED THEM.

9
00:00:26,750 --> 00:00:29,150
THEY'RE STUCK HERE,
BECAUSE THEY HAVE UNFINISHED
BUSINESS WITH THE LIVING

10
00:00:29,150 --> 00:00:30,450
AND THEY COME TO ME
FOR HELP.

11
00:00:34,550 --> 00:00:36,050
IN ORDER TO TELL YOU
MY STORY,

12
00:00:36,650 --> 00:00:37,750
I HAVE TO TELL YOU THEIRS.

13
00:00:44,550 --> 00:00:45,750
Melinda: SO HOW LONG
WERE THEY MARRIED?

14
00:00:45,950 --> 00:00:46,750
Delia:
JUST A FEW MONTHS.

15
00:00:47,250 --> 00:00:48,450
HE WAS SO CRAZY ABOUT HER.

16
00:00:49,250 --> 00:00:50,550
HOW COME HE
NEVER BROUGHT HER
INTO THE STORE?

17
00:00:51,150 --> 00:00:54,650
I DON'T KNOW. MAYBE HE
WAS JUST TRYIN' TO BUY HER
THINGS TO SURPRISE HER.

18
00:00:55,750 --> 00:00:58,250
HE IS A GREAT CUSTOMER
AND SO SWEET.

19
00:00:58,950 --> 00:01:00,450
ANYWAY, WE DON'T
HAVE TO STAY THAT LONG.

20
00:01:05,350 --> 00:01:06,050
JAKE.

21
00:01:07,750 --> 00:01:08,250
HOW ARE YOU?

22
00:01:10,550 --> 00:01:11,850
YOU REMEMBER
MY FRIEND MELINDA.

23
00:01:12,050 --> 00:01:13,050
OH, HI.

24
00:01:13,050 --> 00:01:14,450
I'M SO SORRY
FOR YOUR LOSS.

25
00:01:14,650 --> 00:01:16,350
THANK YOU.
THANK YOU FOR COMING.
I APPRECIATE IT.

26
00:01:16,450 --> 00:01:17,750
I'M GONNA GO
PAY MY RESPECTS.

27
00:01:19,350 --> 00:01:20,350
Delia: IS THERE
ANYTHING I CAN DO?

28
00:01:20,350 --> 00:01:22,050
NO. EVERYTHING'S
BEEN DONE....

29
00:01:29,250 --> 00:01:30,250
THAT'S HIS WIFE?

30
00:01:32,950 --> 00:01:33,750
TELL ME ABOUT IT.

31
00:01:35,350 --> 00:01:36,550
WHAT'S WRONG
WITH THIS PICTURE?

32
00:01:37,450 --> 00:01:39,350
I LAND THE RICHEST GUY
IN DRISCOLL COUNTY,

33
00:01:39,350 --> 00:01:41,250
AND MY HEART GIVES OUT.

34
00:01:41,850 --> 00:01:43,250
OH. WOW. YEAH.

35
00:01:44,050 --> 00:01:45,850
THIS IS LIKE
POETIC INJUSTICE.

36
00:01:46,350 --> 00:01:46,950
I'M SORRY.

37
00:01:52,750 --> 00:01:54,350
ARE YOU INTERESTED
IN CROSSING OVER?

38
00:01:54,450 --> 00:01:55,250
YOU MEAN THAT LIGHT?

39
00:01:55,250 --> 00:01:58,150
YEAH. I REALLY THINK
YOU SHOULD GO
INTO THAT LIGHT,

40
00:01:58,150 --> 00:01:59,150
YOU'LL
FIND PEACE THERE.

41
00:01:59,150 --> 00:02:02,850
PEACE. I'M THIRTY--
28 YEARS OLD.

42
00:02:03,650 --> 00:02:04,950
WHAT DO I WANT WITH PEACE?

43
00:02:06,650 --> 00:02:10,350
BESIDES, I--
I REALLY DID LOVE HIM.

44
00:02:11,350 --> 00:02:12,150
EVERYTHING OK?

45
00:02:14,650 --> 00:02:17,350
YOU DIDN'T TELL ME
THAT HIS WIFE
WAS SO YOUTHFUL.

46
00:02:17,550 --> 00:02:19,350
OH, I--
I THOUGHT
YOU KNEW.

47
00:02:20,050 --> 00:02:20,850
NICE JACKET.

48
00:02:21,750 --> 00:02:22,750
SHE LIKES YOUR JACKET.

49
00:02:22,750 --> 00:02:23,950
OH, THANK--

50
00:02:27,450 --> 00:02:28,050
NO.

51
00:02:28,350 --> 00:02:29,050
YES.

52
00:02:30,050 --> 00:02:31,050
IS THAT SUPPOSED
TO HAPPEN?

53
00:02:31,050 --> 00:02:31,850
WHAT?

54
00:02:32,150 --> 00:02:33,950
THE LIGHT, IT'S--
IT'S LIKE...

55
00:02:34,850 --> 00:02:37,650
IT'S NOT SO BRIGHT ANYMORE,
LIKE THERE'S SOMETHING
GETTING IN THE WAY.

56
00:02:39,250 --> 00:02:40,250
OH, THAT'S FREAKY.

57
00:02:40,450 --> 00:02:41,050
WHAT IS?

58
00:02:41,650 --> 00:02:42,950
I'M GONNA GO HANG
SOMEWHERE ELSE.
MELINDA...

59
00:02:42,950 --> 00:02:44,150
THIS IS TOO CREEPY.

60
00:02:45,650 --> 00:02:46,450
WHAT'S GOING ON?

61
00:02:47,650 --> 00:02:48,550
I'LL TELL YOU LATER.

62
00:02:49,150 --> 00:02:50,350
GONNA GO FIND
THE LADIES' ROOM.

63
00:02:53,750 --> 00:02:55,150
Man: STOP CRYING.
I'M NOT DEAD!

64
00:02:56,350 --> 00:02:57,650
I'M RIGHT HERE!
LOOK AT ME!

65
00:02:59,350 --> 00:03:00,750
WHAT IS WRONG
WITH YOU PEOPLE?

66
00:03:15,650 --> 00:03:16,750
YOU'RE VERY CONFUSED
RIGHT NOW.

67
00:03:19,650 --> 00:03:20,650
IT'S A DIFFICULT TIME.

68
00:03:21,250 --> 00:03:22,750
HOW COME YOU CAN SEE ME
AND THEY CAN'T?

69
00:03:22,750 --> 00:03:23,850
THAT'S A LONG STORY.

70
00:03:25,550 --> 00:03:26,450
THE IMPORTANT
THING IS...

71
00:03:27,750 --> 00:03:28,750
THERE'S A BETTER
PLACE FOR YOU.

